      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1749: The enable state is snapshotted before loading, but it is not revalidated before performing the deferred load. If another thread disables the account after this block releases configurationMutex_, doRegister() will still synchronously load conversations for a disabled account, which violates the new deferral behavior and can reintroduce startup/work cost for disabled accounts. Recheck the state immediately before loading, or keep the load decision tied to a stable registration transition. For example:\n```suggestion\n    if (shouldLoadConversations) {\n        std::lock_guard lock(configurationMutex_);\n        shouldLoadConversations \u003d autoLoadConversations_ \u0026\u0026 isUsable();\n    }\n    if (shouldLoadConversations) {\n        if (auto* cm \u003d convModule())\n            cm-\u003eloadConversationsIfNeeded();\n    }\n```",
